TEXT.P:
The 10 listed companies enjoying the largest turnover in Monday's
trading were: Ever Fortune Industries; Picvue Electronics; ASE;
United Micro Electronics; ACER; Siliconware Precision Industries Co.;
Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing; Compal Electronic, Inc.; Holtek
Microelectronics; and Mitac International Corp.

The Clinton administration is urged to take positive steps in
handling US-China relations in the following 10 areas: a bipartisan
China policy; frequent meetings with administration officials;
frequent exchange with Congress; promotion of human rights; help
China with the rule of law; encourage China and Taiwan rapport;
promote cultural and educational exchanges; expand trade and export;
global stability and security; and assistance with environmental and
urban development.

Western markets, meanwhile, have been booming over the same
period, with Frankfurt gaining 46.14 percent; London, 27.04 percent;
New York, 21.40 percent; and Toronto, 18.92 percent.

The 10 listed companies enjoying the largest turnovers on
Monday's trading were: United Micro Electronics; Taiwan Semiconductor
Manufacturing; Mitac International Corp.; Kinpo Electronics; ASE;
Ever Fortune Industries; Carnival; Silicon Integrated Systems Corp.;
The Medium Business Bank of Taitung; and Winbond Electronics Corp.

-- "The Republic of China on Taiwan is a sovereign state. The
destiny of the 21 million citizens of Taiwan should be decided by
themselves. We believe that the US will not harm Taiwan's interests;
however, we are worried that during the Clinton-Jiang summit, the PRC
will pressure the US to advocate positions that may be detrimental to
Taiwan;

III -- As a strong economic power, Taiwan hopes to take part in
international activities to make a greater contribution to the
international community;

However, once the summit is over, Premier Vincent Siew will leave
for a visit to Togo, Solomon Islands and Fiji between July 2-9,
probably via Australia or the US.

-- Demand that the mainland authorities recognize their mistake
in conducting the June 4 military oppression at Tiananmen Square and
punish those responsible for the killing;

-- Ask mainland China to allow freedom of speech, dissemination
and association, and to follow international conventions on human
rights;

-- Clinton's visit is a diplomatic event, and there is no
precedent of mainland media being permitted to transmit live
broadcasts of diplomatic activities;
